<h4 style="font-family: arial; text-align: center;">
  <span style="font-size: medium; color: black">
    "Business people who read at least seven business books a year<br />
    earn over 2.3 times more<br />
    than those who read only one per year."
  </span>
</h4>

<p style="font-family: arial; text-align: center;">
  <a href="https://wordsrated.com/business-books-statistics/" style="color: #b4445c;" target="_blank">
    <span style="font-size: small;">Source: Business Book Sales Statistics</span>
  </a>
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  While I won't promise results on the level of Elon Musk or Tony Robbins, the books that follow are most likely to add value to your career. So say the business experts. So say the readers.
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  For the 13th year in a row Beantown Web has conducted a quasi-scientific meta-search to identify the best business books published during the calendar year. This year's search began by identifying 15 "Best of" lists. This resource list is available upon request. The final results are presented here.
</p>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  A total of 199 unique books were mentioned on at least one "Best of" list. Among the unique books, 161 were mentioned only once and 38 received multiple recommendations.</p>

<h3 style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
  The Honorable Mention Shelf
</h3>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  Of the 38 multiple recommendations, 28 books were mentioned on two lists. These books comprise the <b>Honorable Mention</b> list.
</p>

<h3 style="font-family: arial; font-size: large; margin: 10px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; text-align: left;">
  The Must-Read Shelf
</h3>

<p style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  Of the 10 remaining book recommendations, four were mentioned on three lists. These books comprise the <b>Must-Read</b>&nbsp;list:</p>

<ul style="font-family: arial; font-size: medium; text-align: left;">
  <li>
    <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/45320360-a-world-without-work" target="_blank">
      <b>A World Without Work</b>
    </a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/49689484-competing-in-the-age-of-ai" target="_blank">
      <b>Competing in the Age of AI</b>
    </a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/44064568-reimagining-capitalism-in-a-world-on-fire" target="_blank">
      <b>Reimagining Capitalism in a World on Fire</b>
    </a>
  </li>
  <li>
